VISA POLICY OF NORTH KOREA Visitors to North Korea must obtain a visa from one of the North Korean diplomatic missions .
VISA POLICY MAP VISA EXEMPTION Section::::Visa exemption .
As of April 2017 holders of normal passports of all countries require a visa to visit North Korea .
All visitors traveling for tourism require an authorization from a North Korean travel agency .
An exception exists for Chinese tourists visiting only the Tongnim County who can stay in this county using the Chinese ID card instead of a visa and passport for up to two days .
Most nationals may also visit Sinuiju for a day trip without a visa .
Holders of diplomatic or service passports issued to nationals of the following countries can visit North Korea without a visa : valign =
top Nationals of South Korea seeking to visit North Korea must submit the North / South Korea visitation verification certificate and the Departure card to the Immigration Officer at the immigration port and go through immigration inspection .
